    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-03T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="716"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.51/7–146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-03T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 3, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>492. 1. Embstels 719 and 720, July 1.<note n="41" xml:id="d716fn41">Neither
                        printed.</note> No foundation for <gloss target="#t_AP1">AP</gloss> despatch
                    re $100 million loan. Despatch apparently result irresponsible misinterpretation
                    of interview with Dept.</p>
                <p>2. With approval National Advisory Council, <gloss target="#t_Eximbank1"
                        >Eximbank</gloss> approved today participation up to $25 million in exporter
                    credits for Turkey. Total amount of exports this credit will finance depends on
                    private credits which may be advanced by exporters or private banks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
